<Link id="l00009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="9"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\file Pass to transform amx intrinsics to scalar operations.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="10"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This pass is always enabled and it skips when it is not -O0 and has no</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="11"><Highlight kind="comment">/// optnone attributes. With -O0 or optnone attribute, the def of shape to amx</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="12"><Highlight kind="comment">/// intrinsics is near the amx intrinsics code. We are not able to find a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="13"><Highlight kind="comment">/// point which post-dominate all the shape and dominate all amx intrinsics.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="14"><Highlight kind="comment">/// To decouple the dependency of the shape, we transform amx intrinsics</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="15"><Highlight kind="comment">/// to scalar operation, so that compiling doesn&#39;t fail. In long term, we</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="16"><Highlight kind="comment">/// should improve fast register allocation to allocate amx register.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="17"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
